Package: OmopNsaidGiBleedStudy
Type: Package
Title: Comparative New-User Cohort Study of NSAID Gastrointestinal Safety in the OMOP CDM
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Agniva Das
Maintainer: Agniva Das <agniva.d-statphd@msubaroda.ac.in>
Description: A reproducible OHDSI-framework real-world evidence study estimating the
    comparative risk of gastrointestinal haemorrhage among new users of selective versus
    non-selective NSAIDs, using propensity-score adjustment and empirical calibration on
    OMOP-CDM data (Eunomia). Methodological demonstration on public synthetic data.
License: Apache License 2.0
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.2.0)
Imports:
    DatabaseConnector,
    SqlRender,
    Eunomia,
    CohortGenerator,
    FeatureExtraction,
    CohortMethod,
    EmpiricalCalibration
